cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO 

The paper deals with the problem of building extraction in remote sensing images using geometric features. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) as well as computer graphics (cs.GR) since it involves the extraction of geometric features. The use of mid-level geometric representations and the integration of geometric saliency also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. Finally, the problem of building extraction can also be seen as a robotics problem (cs.RO) since it involves the analysis of images for navigation and mapping purposes.
